Steps to uninstall tomcat


Working perfect

🧹 Create Tomcat uninstall script
1️⃣ Create the file
sudo vim uninstall_tomcat.sh
Press i to enter insert mode, then paste everything below.

📄 Paste this script
#!/bin/bash
echo "Stopping Tomcat if running..."
sudo -u tomcat /opt/tomcat/bin/shutdown.sh 2>/dev/null
echo "Killing any remaining Tomcat/Java processes..."
sudo pkill -f tomcat 2>/dev/null
echo "Checking if port 8080 is still in use..."
ss -tulpn | grep 8080 || echo "Port 8080 is free"
echo "Removing Tomcat user..."
sudo userdel -r tomcat 2>/dev/null
echo "Deleting Tomcat installation directory..."
sudo rm -rf /opt/tomcat
echo "Removing downloaded Tomcat archives..."
sudo rm -f /opt/apache-tomcat-*.tar.gz
echo "Removing Tomcat systemd service if it exists..."
sudo rm -f /etc/systemd/system/tomcat.service
echo "Reloading systemd daemon..."
sudo systemctl daemon-reload
echo "Verifying removal..."
ls /opt
id tomcat 2>/dev/null || echo "Tomcat user removed"
echo "✅ Tomcat has been completely removed from this server."

2️⃣ Save the file
Press:
ESC → :wq → Enter


3️⃣ Make the script executable
chmod +x uninstall_tomcat.sh

4️⃣ Run the script
./uninstall_tomcat.sh
